definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  xanthine + H2O -eq- 4-ureido-5-imidazole carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-valine + H2O + NAD+ -eq- 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate + NH3 + NADH.

label.value: phosphatidylethanolamine - Kdo2-lipid A phosphoethanolamine transferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  Kdo2-lipid A + phosphatidylethanolamine -eq- phosphoethanolamine-Kdo2-lipid A + diacylglycerol.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosylmethionine (SAM) to the 1-phosphate group of lipid A.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-keto-4-methylthiobutyrate + L-phenylalanine -eq- phenylpyruvate + L-methionine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-lactate + GTP -eq- 2-phospho-(S)-lactate + GDP.
Catalysis of the reactions -  (KDO)-lipid IVA + CMP-3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonate -eq- KDO2-lipid IVA + CMP, and lipid IVA + CMP-3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonate -eq- (KDO)-lipid IVA + CMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ADP + D-glucose -eq- AMP + D-glucose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ADP + D-fructose 6-phosphate -eq- AMP + D-fructose 1,6-bisphosphate.
A subcomplex of DNA polymerase III composed of the epsilon subunit which has proofreading activity, and the theta subunit which enhances the epsilon subunit's proofreading activity.

label.value: DNA polymerase III, clamp loader complex

definition.value: A heptamer that includes the tau and gamma products of the dnaX gene and the chi|psi subcomplex. Confers structural asymmetry that allows the polymerase to replicate both leading and lagging strands.

label.value: DNA polymerase III, clamp loader chi|psi subcomplex

definition.value: A dimer composed of the chi and psi subunits which is a subassembly of the DNA polymerase III clamp loader complex and serves as a bridge between the DnaX complex and the single-stranded DNA-binding protein (SSB).
Catalysis of the incision of damaged DNA on the 3' side of a lesion, typically at the ninth phosphodiester bond 3' of the damage.
Catalysis of the reaction -  palmitoyl-CoA + protein-cysteine -eq- S-palmitoyl protein + CoA, specific for Ras proteins.
A heterotrimeric complex composed of the subunits RecF, RecO and RecR. Mediates the loading of RecA protein specifically onto SSB-coated gapped DNA during DNA repair.

label.value: methanol-specific methylcobalamin - coenzyme M methyltransferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  a methylated methanol corrinoid protein + coenzyme M -eq- a methanol corrinoid protein + methyl-CoM. This reaction is the transfer of the methyl group from the methylated corrinoid cofactor of a methylamine corrinoid protein to coenzyme M.
Catalysis of the reaction -  monomethylamine + a monomethylamine corrinoid protein -eq- a methylated monomethylamine corrinoid protein + NH3.

A heterotrimeric protein complex composed of a methanol methyltransferase subunit, a corrinoid protein and a methanol-specific corrinoid - coenzyme M methyltransferase subunit. Catalyzes the transfer of a methyl group from methanol to coenzyme M as part of the pathway of methanogenesis from methanol.

label.value: cyclic nucleotide-gated mechanosensitive ion channel activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of an ion by a channel that opens in response to a mechanical stress and when a cyclic nucleotide has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of an ion by a channel that opens when a cyclic nucleotide has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
The function of binding to an anti-sigma factor and stopping, preventing or reducing the rate of its activity.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N(2)-acetyl-L-ornithine + carbamoyl phosphate -eq- N(2)-acetyl-L-citrulline + H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  arginine(out) + ornithine(in) -eq- arginine(in) + ornithine(out).
Catalysis of the ATP-dependent polymerization of arginine and aspartate to multi-L-arginyl-poly-L-aspartic acid (cyanophycin -  a water-insoluble reserve polymer).
Catalysis of the reaction -  agmatine(out) + putrescine(in) -eq- agmatine(in) + putrescine(out).
Catalysis of the reaction -  arginine(out) + agmatine(in) -eq- arginine(in) + agmatine(out).
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-hydroxy-2-ketopimelate -eq- succinate semialdehyde + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indole-3-acetamide + H2O -eq- indole-3-acetate + NH3. Indole-3-acetamide is known as IAM and indole-3-acetate as IAA.
Catalysis of the transfer of methionine from one side of a membrane to the other.
Catalysis of the reaction -  AMP + sulfite + thioredoxin disulfide -eq- 5'-adenylyl sulfate + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tRNA guanine + 7-cyano-7-deazaguanine -eq- tRNA 7-cyano-7-deazaguanine + guanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-aminoadipate + acetyl-CoA -eq- N2-acetyl-alpha-aminoadipate + coenzyme A.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N(2)-acetyl-L-aminoadipate-semialdehyde + NADP+ + phosphate -eq- N(2)-acetyl-L-gamma-aminoadipyl phosphate + NADPH.

Catalysis of the reaction -  delta1-piperideine-6-carboxylate + NAD+ + 2 H2O -eq- 2-aminoadipate + NADH + H+. Delta1-piperideine-6-carboxylate is also known as 2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyridine-2-carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  lysine(out) + cadaverine(in) -eq- lysine(in) + cadaverine(out).
Catalysis of the reaction -  pyruvate + CoA + oxidized flavodoxin -eq- acetyl-CoA + CO2 + reduced flavodoxin.

Catalysis of the reactions -  5-(methylthio)-2,3-dioxopentyl phosphate + H2O -eq- 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one + phosphate -  (1a) 5-(methylthio)-2,3-dioxopentyl phosphate -eq- 2-hydroxy-5-(methylthio)-3-oxopent-1-enyl phosphate -  (1b) 2-hydroxy-5-(methylthio)-3-oxopent-1-enyl phosphate + H2O -eq- 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxobutanoate + coenzyme A -eq- propionyl-CoA + formate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-threonine (or D-allo-threonine) -eq- glycine + acetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactosamine 6-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-tagatose 6-phosphate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + NAD+ + H2O -eq- 3-phospho-D-glycerate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the transfer of glycolate from one side of a membrane to the other. Glycolate is the smallest alpha-hydroxy acid (AHA).
Catalysis of the reduction of crotonyl-CoA to butyryl-CoA.
Catalysis of the hydration of mesaconyl-CoA to beta-methylmalyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  malate(out) + Na+(out) -eq- malate(in) + Na+(in).
Catalysis of the reaction -  malate + H+ -eq- L-lactate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + corrinoid protein -eq- CO + methylcorrinoid protein + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CO + H2O + oxidized ferredoxin -eq- CO2 + reduced ferredoxin.

The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a carboxysome, an organelle found in the Cyanobacteria consisting of a proteinaceous coat and enzymes for the fixation of carbon dioxide.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  melibiose(out) + Na+(out) -eq- melibiose(in) + Na+(in).
